      • setParameters

        protected void setParameters(int type,
                             List<NameValuePair> parameters)
        Sets the given parameters of the given type as the list of parameters handled by this variant.

        The names and values of the parameters are expected to be in decoded form.

        Parameters:
        type - the type of parameters
        parameters - the actual parameters to add
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if parameters is null.
        Since:
        2.5.0
        See Also:
        getParamList(), NameValuePair.TYPE_QUERY_STRING, NameValuePair.TYPE_POST_DATA
